      "content": "but \"embracing the struggle\" just sounds like a way to romanticize suffering. if the outcome is always zero, then the struggle itself is just unnecessary friction. isn't there a certain logic to the idea that if existence is inherently devoid of purpose, then the most rational response is to simply stop fighting? to stop participating in the absurdity?",
